# Downloads Directory

This directory contains the Persuaid.dmg file for production downloads.

## Building and Deploying the DMG

1. **Build the DMG file:**
   ```bash
   npm run desktop:build
   ```
   This will:
   - Build the Next.js app
   - Build the Electron app and create the DMG
   - Automatically copy the DMG to `public/downloads/Persuaid.dmg`

2. **The DMG file will be available at:**
   - Local: `http://localhost:3000/downloads/Persuaid.dmg`
   - Production: `https://your-domain.com/downloads/Persuaid.dmg`

3. **For Vercel deployment:**
   - The DMG file in `public/downloads/` will be deployed automatically
   - Users can download it from the `/download` page
   - Make sure to commit the DMG file to git (or use a CI/CD pipeline to build it)

## Note
The DMG file is large (~50-100MB typically). Consider:
- Using Git LFS for the DMG file
- Or building the DMG in CI/CD and uploading to a CDN
- Or hosting the DMG on a separate file hosting service
